A 16-year-old boy who tried to cool off drowned in the Umgeni River in Kwadabeka on yesterday afternoon, IPSS Medical Rescue said.The boy had apparently swum near the weir before getting into trouble, according to a statement by paramedics.Police divers recovered his body five metres under water.An inquest docket was opened.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/teen-who-tried-to-cool-off-drowns-in-umgeni-river-20170127